-- Hungary Stocks: Mol, E-Star Alternativ Shares Move in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-06-04T15:45:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-04/hungary-stocks-mol-e-star-alternativ-shares-move-in-budapest.html
The benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index rose 0.7
percent to 16,494.83 by the close in Budapest.  The following were among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL)  , Hungary’s largest refiner, rose 2.9
percent to 15,900 forint. Mol said it supports the nomination of
Croatia’s economy minister and finance minister as new
supervisory board members at Mol’s INA Industrija Nafte d.d.
unit.  E-Star Alternativ Nyrt. (ESTAR)  , a Hungarian energy
company, plunged the most in 3 1/2 years, after two of its board
members left and the company said it is canceling a project. The
shares fell 15 percent to 1,424 forint, the biggest daily drop
since Oct. 20, 2008.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
